The paper deals with the problem of fully decentralized multi-agent reinforcement learning, which involves the use of machine learning algorithms to enable agents to learn from their own experiences and interactions with their environment. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the use of function approximation and communication networks, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), control systems (cs.SY), and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.MA, followed by cs.AI, cs.SY, and cs.NE.
